%20turnout%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20added%20to%20the%20anxiety%2C%20and%20supporters%20of%20both%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20and%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20are%20perplexed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPollsters%20Enjoy%20The%20Spotlight%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20conducting%20exit%20polls%20are%20having%20a%20field%20day%20as%20they%20are%20quizzed%20on%20social%20media%20and%20in%20TV%20interviews.%20However%2C%20given%20that%20it%20is%20unethical%20to%20speak%20about%20such%20details%20with%20elections%20still%20underway%2C%20most%20such%20pollsters%20have%20refrained%20from%20giving%20numbers.%20In%20fact%2C%20among%20them%2C%20many%20are%20those%20who%20give%20different%20answers%20in%20different%20interviews%2C%20adding%20to%20the%20confusion.%20A%20season%20of%20speculation%20and%20a%20battle%20of%20narratives%2C%20and%20amidst%20this%2C%20both%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%20are%20trying%20to%20turn%20the%20public%20sentiment%20in%20their%20favour.%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20has%20already%20claimed%20that%20the%20BJP%20has%20won%20270%20seats%20till%20Phase%204.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElections%20are%20a%20lot%20about%C2%A0%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3Emahaul%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Ethat%20is%2C%20the%20public%20mood.%20India%20has%20many%20late%20deciders%20(25-30%25%2C%20according%20to%20various%20surveys)%2C%20and%20it's%20these%20voters%20who%20are%20swayed%20the%20most%20by%20the%20poll%20discourse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Ground%20Reports%20May%20Be%20Unreliable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20believe%20that%20the%20BJP%20could%20lose%20this%20election%20often%20cite%20the%20example%20of%202004%2C%20when%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%20a%20public%20favourite%2C%20lost%20the%20mandate.%20Almost%20all%20exit%20polls%20had%20failed%20to%20gauge%20the%20public%20mood%20back%20then.%20If%20exit%20polls%20conducted%20through%20scientific%20techniques%20can%20go%20wrong%2C%20ground%20reports%2C%20based%20on%20unscientific%20sampling%20methods%20and%20gathered%20through%20ground%20feedback%2C%20can%20also%20be%20misleading.%20This%20is%20because%20such%20local%20reports%20usually%20tend%20to%20portray%20elections%20as%20%E2%80%98pitched%20battles'%2C%20with%20supporters%20of%20each%20camp%20claiming%20that%20victory%20is%20theirs.%20This%20was%20seen%20even%20in%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20state%20elections%20in%202023%2C%20which%20largely%20became%20a%20one-sided%20battle%C2%A0in%20the%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Flok-sabha-polls-2024-why-are-young-voters-staying-away-from-elections-what-are-their-concerns-785352%3Fhp%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Why%20Are%20Young%20Voters%20Staying%20Away%20From%20Elections%3F%20What%20Are%20Their%20Concerns%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20look%20at%20some%20data.%20In%20the%201999%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20182%20seats%20with%20a%2024%25%20vote%20share%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20won%20114%20with%2028%25%20votes.%20Though%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20vote%20shares%20of%20the%20two%20was%20just%204%20percentage%20points%20(pp)%2C%20the%20BJP%20still%20managed%20to%20form%20a%20government%20with%20the%20support%20of%20NDA%20allies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20next%20general%20elections%20in%202004%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20138%20seats%20(-44)%20with%20a%2022%25%20vote%20share%20(-2%20pp)%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20won%20145%20(%2B31)%20with%20a%2027%25%20vote%20share%20(-1%20pp).%20The%20Congress%20formed%20a%20government%20with%20its%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(UPA)%20allies%2C%20and%20the%20BJP%20was%20handed%20a%20shock%20defeat%20despite%20its%20%E2%80%98India%20Shining'%20campaign.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20Victory%20Margins%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201999%2C%20the%20BJP's%20average%20lead%20on%20the%20seats%20it%20won%20was%20around%2065%2C000%20in%20terms%20of%20votes%20and%C2%A09%20pp%20in%20terms%20of%20vote%20share.%20A%20victory%20margin%20of%2010%20pp%20is%20usually%20considered%20a%20close%20contest%20as%20a%20swing%20of%20only%205%20pp%20is%20enough%20to%20reverse%20the%20mandate.%20The%20BJP%20victory%20in%201999%20was%20thus%20not%20huge%2C%20which%20is%20partly%20why%20it%20lost%20to%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20next%20general%20election.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20BJP's%20average%20winning%20margin%20for%20its%20victory%20seats%20was%20around%202.32%20lakh%20votes%20and%C2%A020%20pp%20in%20terms%20of%20vote%20share.%20A%20victory%20margin%20of%2020%20pp%20is%20considered%20a%20one-sided%20contest%20as%20a%20swing%20of%20more%20than%2010%20pp%20is%20needed%20to%20tilt%20the%20contest.%20Can%20this%20huge%20margin%20be%20reversed%20in%202024%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Felections-2024-why-brand-modi-is-unlikely-to-fizzle-out-anytime-soon-5337896%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%20Opinion%3A%20Elections%202024%3A%20Why%20Brand%20Modi%20Is%20Unlikely%20To%20Fizzle%20Out%20Anytime%20Soon%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201984%20elections%2C%20even%20though%20the%20Congress%20won%20414%20seats%20with%20an%20average%20vote%20share%20lead%20of%2022%20pp%2C%20it%20lost%20the%20subsequent%20elections%20in%201989.%20Notably%2C%20what%20also%20helped%20the%20party%20in%201984%20was%20the%20deep%20sympathy%20generated%20after%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20assassination.%20That%20waned%20by%20the%20next%20election%2C%20and%20the%20Bofors%20scandal%20and%20corruption%20allegations%20against%20the%20Gandhi%20family%20cost%20it%20dear.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20there%20comes%20the%20question%3A%20is%20the%20political%20climate%20in%20India%20today%20similar%20to%201984%20or%202004%2C%20or%202019%3F%20Well%2C%20the%20answer%20depends%20on%20which%20side%20of%20the%2