ki%2C%2025%2C%20was%20charged%20with%20fraud%20over%20C%245%2C000%20and%20laundering%20the%20proceeds%20of%20crime%20on%20May%202%2C%20Durham%20Regional%20Police%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20Pleterski's%20associate%2C%20Colin%20Murphy%2C%2027%2C%20was%20also%20charged%20with%20fraud%20and%20released%20on%20an%20undertaking%2C%20the%20statement%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20men%20were%20charged%20following%20a%2016-month%20investigation%20after%20police%20began%20receiving%20numerous%20complaints%20starting%20July%202022%20about%20an%20investment%20fraud.%20The%20investigation%20revealed%20that%20the%20two%20were%20%26quot%3Bgenerating%20large%20weekly%20profits%20through%20savvy%20investments%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20victims%20were%20ultimately%20%26quot%3Bdefrauded%26quot%3B%20and%20unable%20to%20recover%20their%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202022%2C%20an%20Ontario's%20Superior%20Court%20ordered%20Pleterski%20and%20his%20company%2C%20AP%20Private%20Equity%20Ltd%2C%20into%20bankruptcy%20and%20appointed%20Grant%20Thornton%20Ltd%20as%20trustee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAiden%20Pleterski%20received%20C%2441.5%20million%20in%20investment%20funds%20but%20only%201.6%25%20of%20that%20sum%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20invested%2C%20according%20to%20court%20records%20posted%20online%20by%20Grant%20Thornton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPleterski%2C%20who%20was%20released%20on%20a%20C%24100%2C000%20bail%20with%20his%20parents%20signing%20as%20sureties%2C%20is%20required%20to%20hand%20in%20his%20passport%20to%20the%20Durham%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichael%20Simaan%2C%20a%20lawyer%20who%20has%20represented%20Pleterski%20in%20the%20past%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20calls%20for%20comment%20from%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPleterski%2C%20who%20has%20over%20100%2C000%20social%20media%20followers%2C%20would%20flaunt%20his%20travels%20and%20several%20luxury%20cars%2C%20including%20Lamborghinis%20and%20McLarens.%3C%2Fp%3E